ZH: 我们不应该分手。
EN: We shouldn't break up.

ZH: 他们决定分手。
EN: They decided to break up.

ZH: 他们分手了。
EN: They broke up.

ZH: 我们已经分手了。
EN: We have already broken up.

ZH: 你不要再提分手。
EN: Don't bring up breaking up again.

ZH: 他们的分手很突然。
EN: Their break up was very sudden.

ZH: 分手是我唯一的选择。
EN: Breaking up is my only choice.

ZH: 我们尝试修复我们的关系，但最终还是决定分手。
EN: We tried to repair our relationship, but ultimately decided to break up.

ZH: 我觉得我们之间不应该再继续下去，我们应该分手。
EN: I feel like we shouldn't continue anymore, we should break up.

ZH: 分手时很痛苦。
EN: Breaking up is painful.

ZH: 我们分手后仍保持朋友关系。
EN: We remained friends after breaking up.

ZH: 分手带给人们很多伤害。
EN: Breaking up causes a lot of hurt.

ZH: 这段感情已经到了该结束的时候了，我们应该分手。
EN: This relationship has come to an end, we should break up.

ZH: 我们之间的矛盾无法解决，只能选择分手。
EN: Our conflicts are unsolvable, we can only choose to break up.

ZH: 我们之间的感情已经破灭了，我们应该分手。
EN: Our feelings have faded, we should break up.

ZH: 无论发生什么事情，我们都不会轻言分手。
EN: No matter what happens, we won't easily break up.

ZH: 他们的分手波及了所有的朋友和家人。
EN: Their break up affected all their friends and families.

ZH: 我们曾经相爱，但现在必须分手。
EN: We used to love each other, but now we must break up.

ZH: 感情一旦出问题，就很难避免分手。
EN: Once feelings are troubled, it's difficult to avoid breaking up.

ZH: 他们的感情渐行渐远，最后不得不分手。
EN: Their relationship drifted apart over time, and eventually had to break up.
